/*
:name: cond_modified_read
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: cond_modified_read.condread
:pyrope_top: cond_modified_read.condread
*/

// Regression (constprop miscompile, the slang `g = e && b` shape): a var
// conditionally modified under an uncertain arm is pinned to nil by
// Symbol_table::leave_scope (the cassert-discharge contract). A downstream
// VALUE read through a comparison/logic chain used to fold that nil into
// the chain, drop the producers, and leave a dangling ref that tolg wired
// to 0sb? poison — the whole `e` wire vanished from the output cone. The
// uncertain-nil MARK now propagates through eq/ne and log_* folds, keeping
// every producer alive so tolg lowers the real wires.
comb condread(s:bool, b:bool) -> (g:bool) {
  mut e = false
  if s {
    e = true
  }
  g = e and b
}
